THE month of love has people smitten and in love with their partners. It is the same for rising DJ and producer DJ Patlama whose upcoming single Ngikhethe Wena is inspired by the perfect love. The musician, whose real name is Thabo Phallane (45), released the single on Friday, 18 February. The single has been enjoying phenomenal play on various radio stations. DJ Patlama said he will shoot the music video on 3 March in Rustenburg. “Ngikhethe Wena is basically about this guy who inspired his lady to be better, do more with her life, follow her dreams, and be passionate. ALSO READ : INSIDE DUMI MKOKSTAD AND ZIPHOZENKOSI’S GENDER REVEAL PARTY! “They have the perfect relationship that never fails to fuel inspiration, hence the title. It’s an Afro-tech single.” He said it is available on all digital music platforms. DJ Patlama, who hails from Mabopane in Tshwane, said his journey into music hasn’t been easy, but he is pushing because he is passionate about it. “It has been a tough ride, but my love of music and being consistent have made it easy,” he said. DJ Patlama said his music that’s out is doing very well and he is proud of himself for doing well. He said he is working on more music.